ENTRY            E2105   20260503   20260508   20260508       E158
SUBENT        E2105001   20260503   20260508   20260508       E158
BIB                 12         33
TITLE      Differential cross section and analyzing power of the
           pp->pp, pi0 reaction at a beam energy of 390 MeV
AUTHOR     (Y.Maeda, M.Segawa, T.Ishida, A.Kacharava, M.Nomachi,
            Y.Shimbara, Y.Sugaya, K.Tamura, T.Yagita, K.Yasuda,
            H.P.Yoshida, C.Wilkin)
INSTITUTE  (2JPNOSA,2GERJUL,2JPNKYU,2JPNWER)
           (4GRGGRG) High Energy Physics Institute
           (2JPNJPN) Physics Division, Fukui Medical University
           (2UK UK) Physics and Astronomy Department, UCL
REFERENCE  (J,PR/C,77,044004,2008)
PART-DET   (P)
INC-SOURCE Beam intensity is 1 nA.
SAMPLE     - Target is natural.
           - Chemical-form of target is element.
           - Physical-form of target is liquid.
METHOD     Two protons were detected in coincidence, and the
           yield of pi0 events was extracted on the basis of the
           missing-mass spectrum.
           (EDE)
FACILITY   (CYCLO,2JPNOSA) Research Center for Nuclear Physics
DETECTOR   - Detector resolution: better than 2% for 200 MeV
             proton
           - Efficiency: 75-87%
           (SCIN) To deduce energy of scattered protons
           (SCIN) Polarimeter set at 60+-1 degrees were used to
                  monitor the beam polarization.
ANG-SEC    (ANG2-CM,P+P)
           scattering angle theta between relative protons (bin
           size is 30 degrees)
HISTORY    (20081126C) Ty
           (20260301A) MA: modified REACTION, Unit in 002, STATUS
                       in 002-003; deleted EN-SEC in 002-003;
                       added ANG-SEC in 001-003.
ENDBIB              33
COMMON               2          3
EN         ANG2-CM
MEV        ADEG
 390.       90.
ENDCOMMON            3
ENDSUBENT           40
SUBENT        E2105002   20260503   20260508   20260508       E158
BIB                  6          7
REACTION   (1-H-1(P,PI0+P)1-H-1,,DA/DA/DP,PI0/P+P/P+P)
ANG-SEC    (ANG1-CM,PI0)
MOM-SEC    (MOM-SEC,P+P) relative momentum between detective p,p
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-SYS) Total systematic uncertainty
           (ERR-S) Statistical uncertainty
STATUS     (TABLE,,Y.Maeda+,J,PR/C,77,044004,2008) Table 1
HISTORY    (20260301A) MA: Unit: MB/SR/MEVC -> NB/SR2MEVC.
ENDBIB               7
